subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis
. Relatively large (
11–17mm
), reddish to dark brown flies; wing usually uniformly infuscated (with an apical spot in 

P. stigmatica

), head mostly orange with similarly textured and pigmented lower frontal vitta and lower orbital strip; anterior part of clypeus large with lower surface characteristically deflexed. Inner vertical, outer vertical, and postocellar setae usually well developed (postocellar seta absent in 

P. zeta

).
